-- China to Expand Efforts to Prevent Insider Trading, Securities News Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-28T23:36:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/china-to-expand-efforts-to-prevent-insider-trading-securities-news-says.html

          
          
             China will increase efforts against
insider trading by expanding trial registration of individuals
who may have access to privileged market-moving information, the
Shanghai Securities News reported today, citing an unidentified
official with the China Securities Regulatory Commission.  
 The securities regulator will increase efforts to issue
rules on the monitoring and scrutinization of listed companies,
the newspaper reported.  
